    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-216">
    <command xml:space="preserve">examine</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">(Zarb)&#x000A;A young Ghanrion, his skin faintly luminescent like the forest around him. His wide eyes carry both fear and urgent curiosity. He seems eager to communicate.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-217"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-217">
    <command xml:space="preserve">w</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Observation Rock&#x000A;A high cliff with a sweeping view of the entire forest. The bioluminescent canopy stretches endlessly to the east and north. To the WEST, a column of black smoke rises against the sky -- something has crashed on your world.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the EAST, the path descends back into the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-218"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-218">
    <command xml:space="preserve">w</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You step out from the treeline toward the wreckage.&#x000A;&#x000A;A sweep of white searchlight catches you immediately.&#x000A;&#x000A;"CONTACT -- northeast perimeter!" a soldier shouts.&#x000A;&#x000A;Boots hammer the ground. You have no time to run, and no ally to protect you.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;    *** Captured by Humans -- You approached the crash site alone and were detected. Return to the forest, find Xilar in the Ravine, and free him first. ***&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;In that game you scored 0 out of a possible 20, in 3 turns.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;Would you like to RESTART, RESTORE a saved game, QUIT or UNDO the last command?&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-219"/>
    </children>
  </item>
